lt.itakademija.exam

Class Warehouse

  • java.lang.Object
    • lt.itakademija.exam.Warehouse

  • public abstract class Warehouse
extends Object
    This class represents a simplified abstraction of a warehouse.

    This class assumes that the main indicator of a warehouse consumption is an imaginary unit of space. It means that if a warehouse has a total space of 100 and its available space is 50 then it means that it is half full.

    Warehouse has two main objects that it operates:

    • Client - represents an entity that can use this warehouse for keeping their packages.
    • Package - represents an entity that occupies some space in a warehouse.

      • getAvailableSpace

        public abstract int getAvailableSpace()
        Returns available space.

        The following formula is used for computing available space:

        totalSpace = totalSpace - reservedSpace;

        Returns:
        available space.

      • getTotalAvailableSpace

        public abstract int getTotalAvailableSpace()
        Returns a total available space.

        Total available space is computed counting all clients' packages' spaces and subtracting it from total space. That is:

        totalAvailableSpace = totalSpace - sum(for each client sum(for each package space));

        Returns:
        total available space.
